               <head>Bilingual Bustan from collection of Tipu Sultan's Mother</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Būstān by Saʿdī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85129656 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh87002727 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85141345" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4381-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Persian text of Sa'di's Bustan with interlinear Dakhini Urdu translation in vernacular prose </p>
                        <p>English notes at beginning by Randolph Marriatt, January 1843 stating: <q>The Bowstan of Saadi with Hindustanie translation under-lined in red ink. - a present from "Padshah Beigum" - the Widow queen of Hyder Ally Khan, father of Tippo Sultaun of Mysoor to Ths: Marriatt Dt. General, Seringapatam 1800</q>
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated, lacking colophon </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="urd">Persian, Urdu (Dakhini dialect), and English</textLang>
